reviewText: All great movies @ a great price
Was exactly what I was expecting and arrived ahead of schedule by a day.

Mona Lisa is fine (3 stars). Sweethearts not so much (1 star). The chief reason for buying this is Stepmom (5 stars). However, the specs on the case are incorrect, stating that Stepmom is anamorphic widescreen. It isn't. It's 4:3 pan-and-scan (dock 1 star). This is not a problem except in two-shots, but if you're expecting widescreen throughout, you'll be disappointed.

I ought to know by now to check these discs when I receive them. It just never occurred to me than a p&s would be included in a set of widescreen films, especially as this is a relatively new issue.

Step-mom and Mona Lisa Smile are great movies by themselves, so I was excited to find this 3-movie DVD! But America's Sweethearts should just be left off, it was so boring and weird, I made it through 15 minutes before shutting it off...
Very good.  Stepmom reminds me a lot of when I was one.  Right on.
the only really good one is the stepmom
Good movies for my interest in gender.
America's Sweethearts is not great.  But the other two are.
